In his remarks at the Washington Institute for Near East Policy, Gen. James L. Jones emphasizes President Obama's pursuit of a two-state solution for Israel and Palestine. He states that this is in the interests of the United States, Israel, the Palestinians, the Arab countries, and the world. Gen. Jones highlights the strong bonds between the United States and Israel, rooted in history, shared values, democracy, and cooperation in various fields. He acknowledges the challenges faced by Israel in a hostile neighborhood but asserts that Israel will not disappear. He reaffirms America's commitment to Israel's security, stating that there is no space between the two countries on this matter. Gen. Jones calls on leaders in the region to show the courage and leadership demonstrated by Anwar Sadat, King Hussein, and Yitzhak Rabin in working towards peace.